jobs.description:
I worked in the Employment, Pensions and Incentives team in the Sydney office of Herbert Smith Freehills. I advised major companies in industries such as construction, aviation, mining and financial services in relation to industrial relations and general employment matters.

I advised on matters such as:

- industrial litigation involving unions, including in relation to unprotected industrial action and picketing;
- enterprise bargaining;
- employment litigation in State and Federal courts and tribunals;
- unfair dismissal litigation;
- termination of employment;
- contractual issues and employment policies; and
- the application and operation of modern awards and industrial instruments.

general.description:
Vicki specialises in major property projects, commercial leasing, government and public sector tendering and joint venture arrangements. She is also experienced in land titling and acquisitions and disposals.  She advises major government and private sector clients.  In the last year, Vicki has:
-led all property aspects of the $750 million sale of Orica’s chemicals business;
-advised Woollahra Municipal Council on Stage 2 of its redevelopment in Double Bay involving a private public partnership between the Council and Woolworths Limited; 
-advised Nine Entertainment Co on the proposed sale and leaseback of its Sydney headquarters in Willoughby; and
-acted for Perpetual Services on complex leasing matters throughout Australia.

jobs.description:
Specialising in commercial litigation and construction disputes.  

Experience includes:
- investigating disputes and advising clients on how to progress them to meet commercial goals;
- adjudications under the Queenland and Northern Territory security of payment regimes;
- assistance with and instructing Counsel in relation to Magistrates, District, Supreme and Federal Court litigation (originating applications and pleadings); 
- engaging experts and interviewing witnesses;
- assisting with expert determinations with respect to large construction projects in Queensland;
- drafting pleadings and affidavits and other relevant court documentation;
- advocacy in the Queensland Civil and Administrative Tribunal; 
- assistance with front end construction matters including contract reviews; and
- pro bono case work including instructing Counsel in the Federal Court regarding an immigration review and the Planning & Environment Court regarding a contempt charge and drafting letters of advice with respect to financial hardship under the National Credit Code.

